# Things-Oriented Careers

##### Use the information below to match your interests and skills to the careers that are more things-oriented.


## Careers in Computing

<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; text-align: center;">
  <thead>
    <tr style="background-color: #f2f2f2;">
      <th style="border: 1px solid black; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;">Things-Oriented Careers</th>
      <th style="border: 1px solid black; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;">Description</th>
      <th style="border: 1px solid black; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;">Skills/Interests</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; font-weight: bold; padding: 8px;">Robotics Technician</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Designs, builds, and maintains robots used for tasks like manufacturing or surgery</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Precision, Problem-solving, Working with various tools, Curiosity</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; font-weight: bold; padding: 8px;">Cybersecurity Specialist</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Protects computer systems and networks from hackers and other security threats</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Detail-oriented, Logical thinking, Persistence, Analytical skills</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; font-weight: bold; padding: 8px;">Systems Architect</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Designs the overall structure of computer systems to meet the needs of a company or project</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Big-picture thinking, Problem-solving, Logical planning, Organization</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; font-weight: bold; padding: 8px;">Automation Specialist</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Programs machines or systems to perform repetitive tasks efficiently, like warehouse automation</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Attention to detail, Problem-solving, Working with systems, Precision</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; font-weight: bold; padding: 8px;">3D Modeler</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Creates 3D designs for games, movies, or simulations using software tools.</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Creativity, Technical skills, Detail-oriented, Problem-solving</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; font-weight: bold; padding: 8px;">Surgeon (Using Nanotechnology)</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Performs minimally invasive procedures with the help of advanced medical robotics and nanotechnology</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Precision, Problem-solving, Working with tools, Critical thinking</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; font-weight: bold; padding: 8px;">Farmer (Smart Agriculture)</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Uses drones, IoT devices, and precision farming tools to increase crop yields efficiently</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Technical literacy, Analytical skills, Curiosity, Problem-solving</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; font-weight: bold; padding: 8px;">Manufacturing Engineer (IoT Systems)</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Implements IoT-based systems to optimize factory operations and streamline production</td>
      <td style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 8px;">Attention to detail, Logical thinking, Working with tools, Organization</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

## You can also go back to check out careers in the other categories!

